üî• Stay consistent 


===========


1Ô∏è‚É£ What are .tfvars files in Terraform?

.tfvars files store variable values separately from the main Terraform configuration, allowing cleaner and reusable setups.
They help manage multiple environments like dev, test, and prod by providing different variable files.

‚∏ª

2Ô∏è‚É£ When should you use a .auto.tfvars file?

Terraform automatically loads any file ending with .auto.tfvars without specifying it during execution.
This is useful when you want default variable sets to always apply for that environment.

‚∏ª

3Ô∏è‚É£ What is a Terraform Workspace?

A Workspace allows you to manage multiple state files inside the same Terraform configuration.
It helps you separate environments like dev/stage/prod without duplicating code.

‚∏ª

4Ô∏è‚É£ When do you use Workspace vs tfvars?

Workspaces separate state, while tfvars separate values.
Use Workspaces for environment isolation and tfvars for environment configuration.

‚∏ª

5Ô∏è‚É£ What is a Repository in DevOps?

A repository is a storage location for your code, configurations, and version history.
It helps collaboration, tracking changes, and maintaining project integrity.

‚∏ª

6Ô∏è‚É£ What is RBAC in Kubernetes?


Role-Based Access Control manages permissions in Kubernetes based on roles and bindings.
It ensures users, groups, and service accounts have only the required access.

‚∏ª

7Ô∏è‚É£ What is the difference between Role and ClusterRole in Kubernetes RBAC?


A Role gives permissions within a specific namespace.
A ClusterRole gives permissions across the entire cluster.

‚∏ª

8Ô∏è‚É£ What is the difference between RoleBinding and ClusterRoleBinding?


RoleBinding connects a Role to users or service accounts within a namespace.
ClusterRoleBinding connects a ClusterRole to users cluster-wide.

‚∏ª

9Ô∏è‚É£ What is Kubernetes Administration?

Kubernetes administration includes cluster setup, node management, networking, storage, monitoring, and security controls.
Admins ensure clusters are scalable, secure, and always running.

‚∏ª

üîü What is the purpose of kubeconfig in administration?

The kubeconfig file stores cluster connection details like servers, certificates, and contexts.
It allows users and tools to authenticate and access Kubernetes clusters safely.


==========

1Ô∏è‚É£ tfvars = stores environmental variable values
2Ô∏è‚É£ auto.tfvars = loads automatically as default variables
3Ô∏è‚É£ Workspace = separates Terraform state per environment
4Ô∏è‚É£ Workspace vs tfvars = state separation vs value separation
5Ô∏è‚É£ Repository = code storage + version control
6Ô∏è‚É£ RBAC = permission management in Kubernetes
7Ô∏è‚É£ Role = namespace-level permissions
8Ô∏è‚É£ ClusterRole = cluster-level permissions
9Ô∏è‚É£ K8s Admin = manages cluster operations
üîü kubeconfig = stores authentication + cluster access details
